Twenty-seven people were killed and 18injured when an Indonesian airliner flew into electricity linesand tumbled to the ground in an explosive ball of fire, airportofficials said.    The Garuda Indonesia Airways DC-9 crashed yesterday on adomestic flight while carrying 37 passengers and eight crewmembers, an airline spokesman said.    The plane, made by McDonnell Douglas Corp &lt;MD.N>, cost 18mln dlrs and was one of 19 DC-9s in Garuda's fleet of 74 jets. REUTER&#3;